I recently created Hugo Front Matter Tools which is described as&hellip;
A collection of Python scripts desinged to help manage Hugo .md content front matter.
I already have mechanisms in many projects, like this blog, that help me report the last time ANY content was pushed to GitHub, or the last time a Hugo site was compiled. But it would be nice, especially in the case of Rootstalk, if I could save the last git add date/time into an individual file&rsquo;s front matter.
